    "summary": "- Ph.D in Law. authored numerous publications, including books, on international criminal justice and human rights in criminal justice;\n\n - Special Adviser to the ICC Prosecutor Oct 2021 \u2013 present; \n - The Eastern European member (Vice-Chair) of the  United Nations Working Group on Arbitrary Detention 2010-2016;\n  - Trial Attorney and Investigation Team Leader in the  United Nations International Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia 1994-2010;\n  - Deputy Procurator for judicial matters of Odesa region (population over 2 million) 1987-1994;\n  - District Attorney in Odesa region 1976 -1987;\n  - Taught at Mechnikov National University, Odesa, Ukraine 1991 \u2013 1994;\n\n  - Official representative of the ICTY to the UN negotiations for the establishment of the International Criminal Court, 1997-2001;\n - Expert of the selected group of experts which prepared recommendations for the International Criminal Court 2002-2003;\n  - Member of the independent Advisory Panel of the Commission for International Justice and Accountability 2013-2019;\n  - Expert of the International Expert Framework for the Codification of International Criminal Procedure 2008-2011.",
